---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/band/PageHero.astro';
import CtaBand from '../../components/band/CtaBand.astro';
---
<PageLayout
  title="Our Story"
  description="How Favor International started, where the founding conviction came from, and how the work grew across fourteen nations."
>
  <PageHero
    label="Our story"
    title="The conviction Favor was born from."
    promise="A short history. The founding prayer. The fourteen nations the work has reached so far."
    image="/images/gift-bishoftu-tot.jpg"
    imageAlt="GIFT Institute classroom"
    variant="split"
  />

  <section class="band band--white">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <h2>The early years.</h2>
      <p>Favor began with a prayer over northern Uganda during a season of civil war. A small US team made a sustained commitment to the villages no other ministry was reaching. The work started with one Portable Bible School. It grew into four pillars — Evangelism + Discipleship, Education, Community Development, and Economic Empowerment — because the field kept asking for the next thing.</p>

      <h2>The expansion.</h2>
      <p>Within a decade, Favor was operating across South Sudan, Chad, Ethiopia, DRC, Kenya, Sudan, and Burundi. Each field team is led by indigenous leaders. US staff act as long-term partners and donor-care liaisons, not field directors.</p>

      <h2>Today.</h2>
      <p>Favor International runs 18 Village Learning Centers, six accredited schools, four field clinics, three GIFT Institute cohorts a year, and a continuous PBS rotation across fourteen nations. None of that is possible without Favor Partners.</p>

      <p><a href="/about/our-story/founder/">Read the founder's story →</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CtaBand
    heading="Be part of the next chapter."
    body="Favor Partners write the story for the next ten years."
    ctaLabel="Become a Favor Partner"
    ctaHref="/give/partner-monthly/"
    variant="green"
  />
</PageLayout>
